</p>
<p>OHCHR Nepal: Although the previous Army Act (Army Act 1959) did not 
contain any provisions relating to torture or disappearance, Section 62(2) of the 
new Army Act 2006 requires that NA personnel accused of acts &#8220;defined as an 
offence&#8221; of torture and disappearance be tried by a Special Court Martial 
(comprised of an Appellate Court Judge, the Secretary of the Ministry of Defense </p>

