<p>40. Human rights defenders in Nepal 
have tried to use the writ of habeas 
corpus to address the problem of 
disappearances. Obviously, this 
remedy is only relevant to persons 
unlawfully and secretly detained by 
the security forces, and is of no use 
to combat disappearances allegedly 
